Scientists can cut DNA like text — this is how CRISPR works.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:08,800
CRISPR is like a molecular scissors, targeting specific DNA sequences.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:11,600
Imagine fixing genetic errors to prevent diseases.

4
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,200
Sounds like sci-fi, right?

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:18,000
With CRISPR-Cas9, scientists guide RNA to the target DNA, making precise cuts.

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,200
This breakthrough can revolutionize medicine, agriculture, and more!

